*****CLOSED BY THE DEPARTMENT OF HEALTH ON 3/19/2019*****  Qathra is the hipster outpost of Ditmas Park.  It's the quintessential artisanal New York City coffee shop/cafe.  What could better convey the transitional period of the neighborhood?  (Mimi's Humus perhaps?)  There is some good food here but it is most definitely double $$, pushing on $$$ dollar sign.  It use to be cash only and there is still an ATM on-site.  The coffee-obsessed barista has both soy and almond milk for that expresso or Caffè Americano (god forbid you call it anything else).  Portions are small so be warned if you think this could be a suitable spot for a hearty dinner.  I've had a few different dishes here plus coffee, tea, hot coco and some pastries.  The humus plate and chipotle egg dishes are tasty and the coffee is very good (though I am not picky about my hot bean water).  The pastries are good too, although expensive.  Outdoor seating is an added bonus and service usually runs between a little slow and kinda fast.  If you prefer a less yuppie coffee stop you can always head to the Connecticut Muffin just three doors down or Catskill Bagel only a few blocks East.

great vibe. great coffee. haven't eaten the food yet but it looks and smells good. workers are charming and kind. backyard can turn into something of a rowdy day care area reminiscent of park slope. also spotted a kid riding his scooter through the place and it seemed ok with the parents. if you can live with the possibility of being around that, it's a great place to do work and chill with friends.

I hate you, then I love you. Then I love you, then I hate you.  This is how I feel about Qathra. Celine always knows how to sum it up in a song, ay.  Qathra is this cute little hipster spot on Cortelyou and it fits right in with the attitude and vibe of the neighborhood. My first hate is because it's cash only. (It makes me rage... )  I have a love hate relationship with the food. Some dishes are truly sexy, comforting and hearty while others are super meh, bland and you know, nothing to write home about. Like this morning, my Mediterranean eggs with Zaatar were delicious but my friends egg dish had frozen portobello mushrooms. (As if they forgot to defrost it and just dumped it on the plate) who does that?  They do have outdoor seating which is awesome when the weather is nice. And the price to portion ratio is perfect.  So yes Qathra. I hate you, then I love you. Then I love you, then I hate you.
Cozy place with friendly staff. Excellent food and great coffee. They restrict the laptops during busy hours to provide better service. There are tables outside in the back too!

Awesome coffee roast, delicious bakery, and gourmet menu selection combined with friendly service and a cozy atmosphere. Good for to go orders, sit down with friends, or a comfortable place to read or get some work done. Be mindful, no laptops permitted on weekends.
Awesome ethnic brunch with a kick. Great coffee including white cappuccino. Highly recommended!

This place is amazing! The guys here are really great! They are very friendly, professional and courteous.  The food is amazing and the Latte? Just what you need! Lol.  Let's not forget the atmosphere.  A nice cozy place inside, and then (for those nicer weather days), a great relaxing backyard.  Overall? Very amazing cafe shop in Brooklyn!

Good place. For me the nicest things are the decor and the sit-out at the back + the amazing Home-made Almond Croissant. $3.25 a piece and the best I've eaten so far - period. Frankly, this whole review is really about that croissant. Must try those croissants fresh. Coffee, food etc are good too.

This is a cute cafe in my neighborhood that I go to sometimes when I want a latte in the morning or to have breakfast with my out of town guests.  They have good coffee and their breakfast items are pretty tasty.  Remember to get a rewards card so you can get a free coffee after buying 10 coffees.  They have a nice outdoor patio in the back to sit when the weather is warm.  Just a tip - this place is cash only and ask for the wi-fi password.

We love Qathra! My daughter and I come every weekend for a nice early breakfast together (I love that it's open so early). I love Laptop Free Weekends. The food is great... and quick. Ideal with a young kid. The yard is wonderful -- though my daughter misses the fountains with the plastic ducks! But the fact that there is more shade is great.  The only thing I would change is... Please add a diaper changing table (fold down would be fine) in the bathroom -- I hate changing a baby on the floor!
